bug.short_desc: Printing Firefox options, both background colors and frames print control, not working.

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0
1- Even though you do NOT select "Print Background Colors" the background color is printed anyway. It should not print unless selected.
2- Frames: option when on "As Laid Out on the Screen" it only prints one page. If you switch between the Frames: options and print a few wrong ones that only print a page or that separately print every frame on its own page then finally it might work when swtiched back to "As Laid out on screen".
Note: Both of these print problems just started with the last update download of Firefox within I think this last week. I am using Firefox 4.0
Reproducible: Always
Problem two above about frames printing happened when I printed a two page web page but only one page would print. Thus it did not print as seen on screen.
Created attachment 524030 Print Option Page that is not working.
